in article L. 311-3, when the judicial representative for the protection of
adults is a service mentioned in article L. 554-4:

"1° The information notice provided for at 1° of article L. 471-6 is handed
personally to the protected person or, as soon as the state of the
latter does not allow him to gauge its significance, to a member of the
family council if it has been established or, failing that, to a relative, an ally or a
person from his entourage whose existence is known;

"2° The individual document for the protection of adults provided for at 2° of the article
L. 471-6 is also handed to the person;

"3° The protected persons are involved in the service's operation.";

7° In article L. 471-9, the words: "as well as the adaptations made to the
implementation of article L. 311-5 by article L. 471-7" are deleted.

